<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Hide button on the start bar]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=627&amp;p=3143#p3143"><![CDATA[
If by Start bar, you mean the Windows TASK bar, then that is not something Classic Shell modifies the behavior of. Classic Shell only adds a Start button to the taskbar or can make it opaque. Once the taskbar is set to auto hide, a way to show it by mouse is to move the mouse to the edge of the screen where the taskbar is. Or you can hit Win key to show the Start menu or Win+T to show the taskbar only without opening the Start menu.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Tue May 07, 2013 6:02 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
