First of all, great job and thank you, I support your job and tell my friends to do the same. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br />Here is my suggestion (sorry for my English, I'm not a native speaker and since my windows language is not English, I'm not sure the menu names are exactly the same as I will translate them).<br /><br />I use windows 8 mainly on 1366x768 laptops, so i always try to have the more vertical space I can, that's why my start bar is on the right, not on the bottom as usual. sometimes i need to share the space between 2 different windows, that's why i often hide the start menu. <br />i have to right click the bar, than click on options, then toggle the &quot;automatically hide&quot; option and click ok. when i'm done using two different programs at the same time i have to make it reappear going to the right border, right click, options, toggle the same option and ok again.<br /><br />Is it possible to customize the start bar with a toggle, a switch an icon or something else to do this thing with just one click instead of 4? i would be great if you can add such a feature. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />thank you.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=708">nicods</a> — Tue May 07, 2013 1:34 am</p><hr />
